Continuous colours - sequential & diverging

Sequential - 2-colour gradient

pets %>%

             y = weight,
             colour = sleep)) +

pets %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = age,
             y = weight,
             colour = sleep)) +
  geom_point(size = 4) +
  scale_color_gradient(high = "#1b458f",
                       low = "#e51636")

Divergent scale - 3-colour gradient

pets %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = age,
             y = weight,
             colour = sleep)) +
  geom_point(size = 4) +
  scale_color_gradient2(low = "#1b458f",
                        mid = "white",
                        high = "#e51636",
                        midpoint = median(pets$sleep)) +
  theme_bw()

students <- students %>% 
  mutate(school_year = factor(school_year,
         levels = c("Year 7",
                    "Year 8",
                    "Year 9",
                    "Year 10",
                    "Year 11",
                    "Year 12")))
students %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = school_year,
             fill = superpower)) +
  geom_bar()

Manual palette

students %>% 
  distinct(superpower) %>% 
  pull()
[1] "Telepathy"    "Invisibility" "Fly"          "Freeze time" 
students %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = school_year,
             fill = superpower)) +
  geom_bar() +
  scale_fill_manual(
    values = c(
      "Fly" = "#1b458f",
      "Freeze time" = "white",
      "Invisibility" = "orange",
      "Telepathy" = "#e51636"
    )
  )
